<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,268,1075,1098]" pageId="9" pageNumber="58">FIGURE 9</emphasis>
. Left: The male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName box="[561,785,1076,1098]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Chondrolepis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="uluguru">
<emphasis box="[561,785,1076,1098]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="58">Chondrolepis uluguru</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(paratype) (SCC 706). The inset is the dorsal view of 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="58">
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Chondrolepis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obscurior">C. obscurior</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
which has the same blunt projections from the shoulders of the tegumen and the genitalia of the two are generally similar.
</paragraph>
